sentences: Delta Lea Goodrem  (born 9 November 1984) is an Australian singer, songwriter, and actress.
Her debut album, Innocent Eyes (2003), topped the ARIA Albums Chart for 29 non-consecutive weeks.
Her debut album, Innocent Eyes (2003), topped the ARIA Albums Chart for 29 non-consecutive weeks.
Goodrem's second album, Mistaken Identity (2004), was created while she was suffering from cancer.
In 2007, Goodrem released Delta, her third number-one album, which saw another number-one single, "In This Life".
Her fourth studio album, Child of the Universe (2012), produced the single "Sitting on Top of the World".
In 2016, her fifth album, Wings of the Wild, became her fourth number-one album on the ARIA Albums Chart, while giving her another number-one single, "Wings".
Goodrem's most recent and fifth number-one album, Bridge over Troubled Dreams was released May 2021.
She served as a coach on The Voice Australia from 2012 to 2013 and again from 2015 to 2020.

During her one-season hiatus in 2014, she served as a coach on The Voice Kids, and coached eventual winner Alexa Curtis.
